        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 9:25AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 925 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Fourche Valley to near Mimosa to near Albert
Pike Recreation Area to near Umpire to 6 miles west of Gillham.
Movement was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
De Queen, Dierks, Horatio, Umpire, Lockesburg, Gillham, Corinth,
Athens, Center Point, Silver Ridge, Geneva, Muddy Fork, Lebanon,
Burg, and Provo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
